POSITIVELY AWESOME dueled on the outside up the backstretch and around the turn and continued to battle gamely to the wire, narrowly missing. MERU raced in the middle of the pack on the outside through the opening stages, continued around the turn in the three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole, gained ground and was outkicked in the final furlong. JUPITER BLUES raced off the pace up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and improved position in the lane while never threatening the top two. LOVERBOY LOU raced in the middle of the pack on the inside early, navigated the turn from the two path and showed no kick. APACHE raced in the middle of the pack between horses up the backstretch, came around the turn in the three path and was empty in the lane.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: DELAWARE PARK RACE 3 1M 70Y Dirt CR: 52. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. (PLUS UP TO 50% Other Sources) FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 120 lbs.; Older, 123 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250, if for $5,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LILLI ROSE raced in the two path around the first turn, dueled on the outside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the two path around the far turn and drew off in the lane. DESTINED TO DANCE raced in the two path early, trailed the field up the backstretch, began a bid from the three path coming around the second turn and gained ground late. EXAGERADORA stumbled and was blocked leaving the gate, saved ground around the first bend, settled off the pace on the inside for the run up the backstretch, came around the far turn in three path, began a bid approaching the quarter pole and improved position in the lane. BIONIC KAT veered in sharply and bumped with horse inside at the start, raced in the middle of the pack in the two path through the opening half mile, angled in to save ground around the turn and kept on to the finish. PAUL'S TRICKY TALE saved ground around the turn, dueled on the inside up the backstretch, continued to battle from the rail around the second turn and weakened in the stretch. MS KAYS COWGIRL raced in the two path early, came up the backstretch off the pace on the outside, navigated the far turn from the three path and never threatened. RED RIVER SUSI raced in the four path in the middle of the pack around the first turn and up the backstretch, continued around the second turn in the two path and finished evenly. LIFESAWINDINGROAD hopped up leaving the gate, raced in the four path around the first turn, continued up the backstretch at the back of the pack, swung out to the five path coming around the far turn, drifted wider still entering the lane and made no bid. COWGIRL HOP raced in the three path early, stalked the leader on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the far turn from the four path and faded in the stretch. DON'T ANNOY ME bumped with the horse to his outside leaving the gate, saved ground around the first turn, chased the leader on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the far turn in the two path and tired in the lane.

ALLIE'S HALO raced off the pace on the outside early, navigated the turn from the four path and improved position in the lane. IVY WAY raced at the back of the pack on the inside through the opening quarter of a mile, saved ground around the bend and improved position through the stretch. SEA IMAGE tracked the leaders on the inside up the backstretch, continued around the turn in the two path and was outkicked from there. PINK SUNSET trailed the field up the backstretch, saved ground around the bend and never threatened. BEAUTY IN MOTION raced in the middle of the pack between horses through the opening stages, raced in the two path around the turn and showed no kick. LEGGS pressed the pace on the outside up the backstretch, raced in the three path around the turn and tired in the stretch. DIVA OF SEVILLE raced in the middle of the pack on the outside up the backstretch, navigated the turn from the three path and was empty from there.
